properties.description:
Springbrook – bushfire as at 11am Mon 31 Aug. 

Queensland Fire and Emergency Services (QFES) crews are finalising operations following a bushfire near Springbrook Road, Springbrook. This incident is posing no threat to property at this time. There is some smoke haze in the vicinity of the intersection of Springbrook Road and Pine Creek Road. Residents are asked to close windows and doors and if suffering from a respiratory condition, keep medications close by. Motorists should drive with caution and to conditions. If residents are concerned their property is under threat, they are advised to call Triple Zero (000) immediately.

Bloomfield – vegetation fire as at 1.50pm Thur 24 Sept
 
The Rural Fire Service (RFS) is currently on scene at a vegetation fire burning in bushland west of Bloomfield River State School, near Rossville Bloomfield Road, Bloomfield. The fire is currently posing no threat to property. Firefighters are backburning to contain the blaze. Smoke is expected to affect the area for several days. People are asked to close windows and doors and if suffering from a respiratory condition, keep medications close by. Motorists should drive with caution and to conditions. If residents are concerned their property is under threat, they are advised to call Triple Zero (000) immediately.

HAWKWOOD – grass fire as at 3pm Fri 25 Sept
Multiple Queensland Fire and Emergency Services (QFES) crews are currently on scene at a grass fire burning between Burrows Road and Lawes Road. This fire broke out earlier today and is posing no threat to property at this time. Firefighters, with the assistance of water bombing aircraft, are working to control the blaze. Nearby residents may be affected by smoke haze. Residents are asked to close windows and doors and if suffering from a respiratory condition, keep medications close by. Motorists should drive with caution and to conditions. If residents are concerned their property is under threat, they are advised to call Triple Zero (000) immediately.
